==English==

===Etymology===
From Greek [[μετάνοια]] (repentance), compounded from the preposition [[μετά]] (after, with) and the verb [[νοέω]] (to perceive, to think).

===Noun===
'''metanoia'''

# {{religion}} A change of mind, a change of heart.  To be saved by Jesus Christ, one must first change his mind as to what he deems is correct and willing to choose to trust in Christ for salvation.  In English the closest synonym is [[repentance]], but it is not quite the same.  The word [[repentance]] implies a "turning away from sin" or a form of penance.  This is an incorrect interpertation of biblical doctrine. One must first change his mind (metanoia), accept Jesus Christ as savior, then choose to change his life through the power of God.